M5Stack StickS3 - HW B-3 (regulator disable) + B-4 (gpio-keys events) evidence
Captured: 2026-05-30 via esp-idf-monitor on Windows COM9.

B-3: the app blinks the LCD backlight (G38) via the regulator API every ~5 s.
User confirmed (2026-05-30) the screen visibly goes dark and returns ("有閃黑").
This proves regulator_disable()/regulator_enable() cut and restore power on real
hardware. Serial:

>>> Backlight OFF (regulator_disable) - screen should go DARK
>>> Backlight ON (regulator_enable) - screen should be VISIBLE
   (repeated several times over the capture window)

B-4: gpio-keys INPUT-EVENT path confirmed on ESP32-S3 (resolves the earlier
"unconfirmed" caveat). Pressing KEY2 (G12) produced, via the Zephyr input
subsystem (interrupt-driven gpio-keys + INPUT_CALLBACK):

BUTTON code=2 PRESSED      (code 2 = INPUT_KEY_1 = KEY2)
BUTTON code=2 released

Note: only KEY2 was pressed in this run; one full press/release through the
input subsystem is sufficient to confirm the interrupt event path works.
